{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014MBpwz4D4tToGwp8DVnoyu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough information to write the migration plan. Let me summarize what I've found:\n\n**Current State:**\n- Version: CockroachDB v24.1.0 (released 2024/05/15)\n- Next minor version would be v24.2.x or v24.3.x (CockroachDB releases on a quarterly cadence; v24.1 is one release, v24.2 would be the next)\n- Actually, looking at CockroachDB release cadence, they've moved to versions like v24.1, v24.2, v24.3, v25.1, etc. \n\nThe StatefulSet is running 3 replicas with v24.1.0, configured with 1 CPU and 2Gi memory per pod, 25% cache and SQL memory allocation, 10Gi storage, and using a rolling update strategy with parallel pod management in insecure mode.\n\nLooking at the cluster settings, there's an auto-generated secret, diagnostics reporting enabled, and a rebalancing rate limit of 1 MiB set to throttle snapshot operations. The cluster version is pinned at 24.1, and there are some non-default zone configurations being applied to the RANGE default with specific byte limits.\n\nThe system database and various system ranges are configured with 5 replicas despite only having 3 nodes in the cluster, which suggests either under-replication on critical system ranges or a configuration prepared for future scaling. The garbage collection TTL varies across ranges—4 hours for most system ranges, but only 10 minutes for the liveness range. Now I'm working through the upgrade migration plan.\n\nFor upgrading from v24.1 to v24.2, I need to ensure the cluster is healthy first, then set the preserve downgrade option to allow rollback if needed, update the StatefulSet image to trigger a rolling restart of the pods, and finally update the cluster version once all nodes are running the new binary.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_cre