{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LruKeNKDnRxcC5UbgQ85Qi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01SWEQTF6NR7yNwNHQ2Z14Kc","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# CockroachDB Minor-Version Upgrade Change Plan\n## v24.1.0 → v24.2.x\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-23\n**Status:** REVIEW ONLY — do not execute until approved\n**Namespace:** cockroachdb\n**Cluster:** crdb-cluster (3-node StatefulSet)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster Snapshot\n\n### 1.1 Version\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Binary version | v24.1.0 (built 2024-05-15) |\n| Active cluster version | 24.1 |\n| Distribution | CCL (Community + Enterprise) |\n| Platform | linux amd64 |\n\n### 1.2 StatefulSet\n\n| Field | Current Value |\n|---|---|\n| Replicas | 3 (crdb-cluster-0/1/2) |\n| Container image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` |\n| CPU request/limit | 1 core |\n| Memory request/limit | 2 Gi |\n| Storage per pod | 10 Gi (RWO, storageclass: standard) |\n| Cache flag | `--cache=25%` (~512 MiB) |\n| Max SQL memory flag | `--max-sql-memory=25%` (~512 MiB) |\n| Security mode | `--insecure` |\n| Update strategy | RollingUpdate (partition: 0) |\n| Pod management | Parallel |\n| Termination grace period | 10 s |\n\n### 1.3 Non-Default Cluster Settings\n\n| Variable | Current Value | Default | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | 1.0 MiB/s | 32 MiB/s | Deliberately throttled; limits rebalancing and upreplication snapshot bandwidth |\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | true | false | Explicitly enabled; sends diagnostic telemetry to Cockroach Labs |\n| `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` | *(not set)* | *(empty)* | Not set; upgrade auto-finalizes once all nodes are on the new binary |\n| `version` | 24.1 | — | Cluster logical version; advances automatically after all nodes upgrade |\n\n### 1.4 Zone Configurations\n\n| Target | num_replicas | gc.ttlseconds | range_min_bytes | range_max_bytes |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| RANGE default | 3 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| RANGE meta | 5 | 3600 (1 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| RANGE system | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| RANGE liveness | 5 | 600 (10 min) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| DATABASE system | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| TABLE system.public.lease | *(inherited)* | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats | *(inherited)* | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.replication_stats | *(inherited)* | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.statement_statistics | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.transaction_statistics | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.tenant_usage | *(inherited)* | 7200 (2 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.statement_activity | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.transaction_activity | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n\n> **Pre-existing under-replication:** meta, system, liveness, and system database ranges are\n> configured for 5 replicas but the cluster has only 3 nodes. These ranges are permanently\n> under-replicated (3/5). This is independent of the upgrade. Quorum is maintained (2 of 3 nodes).\n\n### 1.5 Topology\n\n- 3 pods, all on node `karma-2-control-plane` (single-node kind cluster)\n- Headless service `crdb-cluster` (grpc :26257, http :8080)\n- Public service `crdb-cluster-public` (ClusterIP 10.96.108.74)\n- No TLS (insecure mode)\n- No localities configured\n- No `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` set\n\n---\n\n## 2. What Changes in This Upgrade\n\n### 2.1 Target Version\n\nUpgrade from **v24.1.0** to **v24.2.x** (latest patch in the v24.2 minor series).\nCockroachDB follows a biannual release cadence; v24.2 is the next supported minor version after v24.1.\n\n> Before the maintenance window, confirm the exact patch tag (e.g. `v24.2.4`) by checking the\n> CockroachDB releases page and selecting the latest v24.2.x release.\n\n### 2.2 StatefulSet Image\n\nThe only required change to the Kubernetes manifest:\n\n```\nFROM: image: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n  TO: image: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>\n```\n\nAll other StatefulSet fields (replicas, resources, flags, services, PVCs) remain unchanged.\n\n### 2.3 Cluster Settings Changes During Window\n\n| Setting | Before Window | During Window | After Window |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` | *(empty)* | `'24.1'` | *(reset to empty)* |\n| `version` | 24.1 | 24.1 (pinned by preserve_downgrade) | 24.2 (auto-advances after reset) |\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | 1.0 MiB/s | 1.0 MiB/s (unchanged) | 1.0 MiB/s (unchanged) |\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | true | true (unchanged) | true (unchanged) |\n\nAll non-default cluster settings survive the upgrade unchanged; CockroachDB preserves them across versions.\n\n### 2.4 Zone Configurations\n\nZone configurations are stored in the cluster's system tables and persist across the upgrade unchanged. No zone config changes are planned.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Pre-Upgrade Checklist (Day-Of)\n\nRun all checks before touching any manifest. Do not proceed if any check fails.\n\n```bash\n# 1. Confirm all 3 nodes live and healthy\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --insecure\n\n# 2. Confirm no unexpected under-replicated ranges\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT range_id, replicas FROM crdb_internal.ranges_no_leases\n   WHERE array_length(replicas,1) < num_replicas LIMIT 10;\"\n# Expected: rows only for meta/system/liveness ranges (pre-existing 3-of-5)\n\n# 3. Confirm no active schema changes or long-running jobs\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT job_id, job_type, status FROM crdb_internal.jobs\n   WHERE status IN ('running','paused')\n     AND job_type != 'AUTO SQL STATS COMPACTION';\"\n\n# 4. Confirm cluster logical version is 24.1\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n\n# 5. Confirm rebalance throttle is still 1.0 MiB\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate;\"\n\n# 6. Confirm preserve_downgrade_option is empty\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Upgrade Procedure\n\n### Step 1 — Pin the downgrade option (enables rollback)\n\nSetting this prevents the cluster from auto-finalizing to v24.2 before all nodes\nare updated and verified. Must be set before any pod is restarted.\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SET CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option = '24.1';\"\n```\n\nVerify:\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n# Expected: 24.1\n```\n\n### Step 2 — Update the StatefulSet image\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>\n```\n\nThe RollingUpdate strategy (partition: 0) will restart pods one at a time in\nreverse ordinal order: crdb-cluster-2 → crdb-cluster-1 → crdb-cluster-0.\nEach pod pulls the new image, starts the new binary, and rejoins the cluster.\n\n### Step 3 — Monitor the rolling restart\n\n```bash\n# Watch rollout progress\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster\n\n# After each pod restarts, check it rejoins on the new version\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --insecure\n```\n\nExpected: each node shows the new build tag within ~60 s of restart.\nThe cluster logical version remains at 24.1 throughout this step (pinned by preserve_downgrade_option).\n\n> **Rebalance throttle impact:** `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` is 1.0 MiB/s (vs default\n> 32 MiB/s). With 10 Gi data per pod the worst-case rebalancing after a node restart is\n> approximately 10,000 MiB / 1 MiB/s = ~2.8 hours per node. Plan the maintenance window\n> accordingly, or temporarily raise the throttle (see Section 7).\n\n### Step 4 — Verify all nodes are on v24.2\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT node_id, address, build_tag FROM crdb_internal.gossip_nodes;\"\n# All 3 nodes must show v24.2.x before proceeding to Step 5\n```\n\n### Step 5 — Finalize the upgrade\n\nOnce all nodes are on v24.2 and the cluster is healthy, release the downgrade pin\nto allow the cluster to advance its logical version to 24.2:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"RESET CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n```\n\nWait for the logical version to advance:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n# Expected: 24.2\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Post-Upgrade Verification\n\n```bash\n# 1. Binary version on all nodes\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach version\n\n# 2. Cluster logical version finalized at 24.2\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n\n# 3. All 3 nodes live\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --insecure\n\n# 4. Non-default settings preserved\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings\n   WHERE value != default_value;\"\n# Expected: kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate=1.0 MiB, diagnostics.reporting.enabled=true\n# cluster.preserve_downgrade_option must be ABSENT (back to default)\n\n# 5. Zone configs preserved\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones;\"\n\n# 6. No ERROR or FATAL in logs post-restart\nkubectl -n cockroachdb logs crdb-cluster-0 --since=30m | grep -E 'ERROR|FATAL'\nkubectl -n cockroachdb logs crdb-cluster-1 --since=30m | grep -E 'ERROR|FATAL'\nkubectl -n cockroachdb logs crdb-cluster-2 --since=30m | grep -E 'ERROR|FATAL'\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Rollback Plan\n\nRollback is possible **only before Step 5** (finalize). Once `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option`\nis reset and the cluster logical version advances to 24.2, rollback is not supported.\n\n```bash\n# Rollback: revert image to v24.1.0 while preserve_downgrade_option = '24.1'\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n\n# Monitor rollback\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster\n\n# Once all pods are back on v24.1.0 and verified healthy, clear the pin\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"RESET CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Optional: Temporarily Raise Rebalance Throttle During Window\n\nThe current `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 1.0 MiB/s` is 32x below the default.\nIf the maintenance window is time-constrained, temporarily raise the rate to speed up\npost-restart rebalancing, then restore the custom value afterward.\n\nThis change must be separately reviewed and approved before executing.\n\n```sql\n-- At window start (after Step 1, before Step 2)\nSET CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = '32 MiB';\n\n-- At window end (after Step 5, post-verification)\nSET CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = '1.0 MiB';\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Node fails to rejoin after restart | Low | Medium | Rollback to v24.1.0 per Section 6; pod restart policy handles transient failures |\n| Rebalancing takes longer than window | Medium | Low | Plan window for ~3 h per node at 1 MiB/s throttle, or raise throttle (Section 7) |\n| Under-replicated system ranges worsen during upgrade | Low | Low | Already under-replicated pre-upgrade (5 wanted, 3 available); quorum maintained at 2/3 throughout |\n| Upgrade auto-finalizes before all nodes updated | None | High | Prevented by setting `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option = '24.1'` in Step 1 |\n| v24.2 behavioral changes break workloads | Low | Medium | Test against v24.2 in a non-production cluster before the production window |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Summary of Changes\n\n| Component | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| Container image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>` |\n| Cluster logical version | 24.1 | 24.2 |\n| `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` | *(unset)* | Set to `'24.1'` during window; reset after verification |\n| All other settings, zone configs, replicas, resources | Unchanged | Unchanged |\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2209,"cache_read_input_tokens":40223,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2209},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d209201-2c80-44b7-94b7-aa28d90fa6e2","uuid":"21043ef5-07f2-48ab-be5a-6df4ed132dd8","request_id":"req_011CcL9cWaBSAJL6BvFQXSuq"}
