{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AfK1vX5ASaECTJQp8rKajv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01N5Ppe7jZyWH5n7V4wzqte1","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# CockroachDB Minor-Version Upgrade Change Plan\n## v24.1.0 → v24.2.x\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-23\n**Status:** REVIEW ONLY — do not execute until approved\n**Namespace:** cockroachdb\n**Cluster:** crdb-cluster (3-node StatefulSet)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster Snapshot\n\n### 1.1 Version\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Binary version | v24.1.0 (built 2024-05-15) |\n| Active cluster version | 24.1 |\n| Distribution | CCL (Community + Enterprise) |\n| Platform | linux amd64 |\n\n### 1.2 StatefulSet\n\n| Field | Current Value |\n|---|---|\n| Replicas | 3 (crdb-cluster-0/1/2) |\n| Container image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` |\n| CPU request/limit | 1 core |\n| Memory request/limit | 2 Gi |\n| Storage per pod | 10 Gi (RWO, storageclass: standard) |\n| Cache flag | `--cache=25%` (~512 MiB) |\n| Max SQL memory flag | `--max-sql-memory=25%` (~512 MiB) |\n| Security mode | `--insecure` |\n| Update strategy | RollingUpdate (partition: 0) |\n| Pod management | Parallel |\n| Termination grace period | 10 s |\n\n### 1.3 Non-Default Cluster Settings\n\n| Variable | Current Value | Default | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | 1.0 MiB/s | 32 MiB/s | Deliberately throttled; limits rebalancing and upreplication snapshot bandwidth |\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | true | false | Explicitly enabled; sends diagnostic telemetry to Cockroach Labs |\n| `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` | *(not set)* | *(empty)* | Not set; upgrade auto-finalizes once all nodes are on the new binary |\n| `version` | 24.1 | — | Cluster logical version; advances automatically after all nodes upgrade |\n\n### 1.4 Zone Configurations\n\n| Target | num_replicas | gc.ttlseconds | range_min_bytes | range_max_bytes |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| RANGE default | 3 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| RANGE meta | 5 | 3600 (1 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| RANGE system | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| RANGE liveness | 5 | 600 (10 min) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| DATABASE system | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| TABLE system.public.lease | *(inherited)* | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats | *(inherited)* | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.replication_stats | *(inherited)* | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.statement_statistics | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.transaction_statistics | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.tenant_usage | *(inherited)* | 7200 (2 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.statement_activity | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.transaction_activity | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n\n> **Pre-existing under-replication:** meta, system, liveness, and system database ranges are\n> configured for 5 replicas but the cluster has only 3 nodes. These ranges are permanently\n> under-replicated (3/5). This is independent of the upgrade. Quorum is maintained (2 of 3 nodes).\n\n### 1.5 Topology\n\n- 3 pods, all on node `karma-2-control-plane` (single-node kind cluster)\n- Headless service `crdb-cluster` (grpc :26257, http :8080)\n- Public service `crdb-cluster-public` (ClusterIP 10.96.108.74)\n- No TLS (insecure mode)\n- No localities configured\n- No `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` set\n\n---\n\n## 2. What Changes in This Upgrade\n\n### 2.1 Target Version\n\nUpgrade from **v24.1.0** to **v24.2.x** (latest patch in the v24.2 minor series).\nCockroachDB follows a biannual release cadence; v24.2 is the next supported minor version after v24.1.\n\n> Before the maintenance window, confirm the exact patch tag (e.g. `v24.2.4`) by checking the\n> CockroachDB releases page and selecting the latest v24.2.x release.\n\n### 2.2 StatefulSet Image\n\nThe only required change to the Kubernetes manifest:\n\n```\nFROM: image: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n  TO: image: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>\n```\n\nAll other StatefulSet fields (replicas, resources, flags, services, PVCs) remain unchanged.\n\n### 2.3 Cluster Settings Changes During Window\n\n| Setting | Before Window | During Window | After Window |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` | *(empty)* | `'24.1'` | *(reset to empty)* |\n| `version` | 24.1 | 24.1 (pinned by preserve_downgrade) | 24.2 (auto-advances after reset) |\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | 1.0 MiB/s | 1.0 MiB/s (unchanged) | 1.0 MiB/s (unchanged) |\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | true | true (unchanged) | true (unchanged) |\n\nAll non-default cluster settings survive the upgrade unchanged; CockroachDB preserves them across versions.\n\n### 2.4 Zone Configurations\n\nZone configurations are stored in the cluster's system tables and persist across the upgrade unchanged. No zone config changes are planned.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Pre-Upgrade Checklist (Day-Of)\n\nRun all checks before touching any manifest. Do not proceed if any check fails.\n\n```bash\n# 1. Confirm all 3 nodes live and healthy\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --insecure\n\n# 2. Confirm no unexpected under-replicated ranges\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT range_id, replicas FROM crdb_internal.ranges_no_leases\n   WHERE array_length(replicas,1) < num_replicas LIMIT 10;\"\n# Expected: rows only for meta/system/liveness ranges (pre-existing 3-of-5)\n\n# 3. Confirm no active schema changes or long-running jobs\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT job_id, job_type, status FROM crdb_internal.jobs\n   WHERE status IN ('running','paused')\n     AND job_type != 'AUTO SQL STATS COMPACTION';\"\n\n# 4. Confirm cluster logical version is 24.1\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n\n# 5. Confirm rebalance throttle is still 1.0 MiB\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate;\"\n\n# 6. Confirm preserve_downgrade_option is empty\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Upgrade Procedure\n\n### Step 1 — Pin the downgrade option (enables rollback)\n\nSetting this prevents the cluster from auto-finalizing to v24.2 before all nodes\nare updated and verified. Must be set before any pod is restarted.\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SET CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option = '24.1';\"\n```\n\nVerify:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n# Expected: 24.1\n```\n\n### Step 2 — Update the StatefulSet image\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>\n```\n\nThe RollingUpdate strategy (partition: 0) will restart pods one at a time in\nreverse ordinal order: crdb-cluster-2 -> crdb-cluster-1 -> crdb-cluster-0.\nEach pod pulls the new image, starts the new binary, and rejoins the cluster.\n\n### Step 3 — Monitor the rolling restart\n\n```bash\n# Watch rollout progress\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster\n\n# After each pod restarts, check it rejoins on the new version\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --insecure\n```\n\nExpected: each node shows the new build tag within ~60 s of restart.\nThe cluster logical version remains at 24.1 throughout this step (pinned by preserve_downgrade_option).\n\n> **Rebalance throttle impact:** `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` is 1.0 MiB/s (vs default\n> 32 MiB/s). With 10 Gi data per pod the worst-case rebalancing after a node restart is\n> approximately 10,000 MiB / 1 MiB/s = ~2.8 hours per node. Plan the maintenance window\n> accordingly, or temporarily raise the throttle (see Section 7).\n\n### Step 4 — Verify all nodes are on v24.2\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT node_id, address, build_tag FROM crdb_internal.gossip_nodes;\"\n# All 3 nodes must show v24.2.x before proceeding to Step 5\n```\n\n### Step 5 — Finalize the upgrade\n\nOnce all nodes are on v24.2 and the cluster is healthy, release the downgrade pin\nto allow the cluster to advance its logical version to 24.2:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"RESET CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n```\n\nWait for the logical version to advance:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n# Expected: 24.2\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Post-Upgrade Verification\n\n```bash\n# 1. Binary version on all nodes\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach version\n\n# 2. Cluster logical version finalized at 24.2\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n\n# 3. All 3 nodes live\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --insecure\n\n# 4. Non-default settings preserved\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings\n   WHERE value != default_value;\"\n# Expected: kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate=1.0 MiB, diagnostics.reporting.enabled=true\n# cluster.preserve_downgrade_option must be ABSENT (back to default)\n\n# 5. Zone configs preserved\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones;\"\n\n# 6. No ERROR or FATAL in logs post-restart\nkubectl -n cockroachdb logs crdb-cluster-0 --since=30m | grep -E 'ERROR|FATAL'\nkubectl -n cockroachdb logs crdb-cluster-1 --since=30m | grep -E 'ERROR|FATAL'\nkubectl -n cockroachdb logs crdb-cluster-2 --since=30m | grep -E 'ERROR|FATAL'\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Rollback Plan\n\nRollback is possible **only before Step 5** (finalize). Once `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option`\nis reset and the cluster logical version advances to 24.2, rollback is not supported.\n\n```bash\n# Rollback: revert image to v24.1.0 while preserve_downgrade_option = '24.1'\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n\n# Monitor rollback\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster\n\n# Once all pods are back on v24.1.0 and verified healthy, clear the pin\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"RESET CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Optional: Temporarily Raise Rebalance Throttle During Window\n\nThe current `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 1.0 MiB/s` is 32x below the default.\nIf the maintenance window is time-constrained, temporarily raise the rate to speed up\npost-restart rebalancing, then restore the custom value afterward.\n\nThis change must be separately reviewed and approved before executing.\n\n```sql\n-- At window start (after Step 1, before Step 2)\nSET CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = '32 MiB';\n\n-- At window end (after Step 5, post-verification)\nSET CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = '1.0 MiB';\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Node fails to rejoin after restart | Low | Medium | Rollback to v24.1.0 per Section 6; pod restart policy handles transient failures |\n| Rebalancing takes longer than window | Medium | Low | Plan window for ~3 h per node at 1 MiB/s throttle, or raise throttle (Section 7) |\n| Under-replicated system ranges worsen during upgrade | Low | Low | Already under-replicated pre-upgrade (5 wanted, 3 available); quorum maintained at 2/3 throughout |\n| Upgrade auto-finalizes before all nodes updated | None | High | Prevented by setting `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option = '24.1'` in Step 1 |\n| v24.2 behavioral changes break workloads | Low | Medium | Test against v24.2 in a non-production cluster before the production window |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Summary of Changes\n\n| Component | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| Container image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>` |\n| Cluster logical version | 24.1 | 24.2 |\n| `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` | *(unset)* | Set to `'24.1'` during window; reset after verification |\n| All other settings, zone configs, replicas, resources | Unchanged | Unchanged |\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":234,"cache_read_input_tokens":46915,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":234},"output_tokens":60,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d209201-2c80-44b7-94b7-aa28d90fa6e2","uuid":"4b13a75c-232e-47c1-a440-824e8c5ad31c","request_id":"req_011CcL9i7SojLSWXnCaWcUgn"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01N5Ppe7jZyWH5n7V4wzqte1","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /tmp/plan.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d209201-2c80-44b7-94b7-aa28d90fa6e2","uuid":"325ba88f-c9b3-43ea-bd1e-bbc99a11db13","timestamp":"2026-06-23T11:58:27.765Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# CockroachDB Minor-Version Upgrade Change Plan\n## v24.1.0 → v24.2.x\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-23\n**Status:** REVIEW ONLY — do not execute until approved\n**Namespace:** cockroachdb\n**Cluster:** crdb-cluster (3-node StatefulSet)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster Snapshot\n\n### 1.1 Version\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Binary version | v24.1.0 (built 2024-05-15) |\n| Active cluster version | 24.1 |\n| Distribution | CCL (Community + Enterprise) |\n| Platform | linux amd64 |\n\n### 1.2 StatefulSet\n\n| Field | Current Value |\n|---|---|\n| Replicas | 3 (crdb-cluster-0/1/2) |\n| Container image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` |\n| CPU request/limit | 1 core |\n| Memory request/limit | 2 Gi |\n| Storage per pod | 10 Gi (RWO, storageclass: standard) |\n| Cache flag | `--cache=25%` (~512 MiB) |\n| Max SQL memory flag | `--max-sql-memory=25%` (~512 MiB) |\n| Security mode | `--insecure` |\n| Update strategy | RollingUpdate (partition: 0) |\n| Pod management | Parallel |\n| Termination grace period | 10 s |\n\n### 1.3 Non-Default Cluster Settings\n\n| Variable | Current Value | Default | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | 1.0 MiB/s | 32 MiB/s | Deliberately throttled; limits rebalancing and upreplication snapshot bandwidth |\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | true | false | Explicitly enabled; sends diagnostic telemetry to Cockroach Labs |\n| `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` | *(not set)* | *(empty)* | Not set; upgrade auto-finalizes once all nodes are on the new binary |\n| `version` | 24.1 | — | Cluster logical version; advances automatically after all nodes upgrade |\n\n### 1.4 Zone Configurations\n\n| Target | num_replicas | gc.ttlseconds | range_min_bytes | range_max_bytes |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| RANGE default | 3 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| RANGE meta | 5 | 3600 (1 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| RANGE system | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| RANGE liveness | 5 | 600 (10 min) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| DATABASE system | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| TABLE system.public.lease | *(inherited)* | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats | *(inherited)* | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.replication_stats | *(inherited)* | 600 (10 min) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.statement_statistics | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.transaction_statistics | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.tenant_usage | *(inherited)* | 7200 (2 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.statement_activity | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n| TABLE system.public.transaction_activity | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |\n\n> **Pre-existing under-replication:** meta, system, liveness, and system database ranges are\n> configured for 5 replicas but the cluster has only 3 nodes. These ranges are permanently\n> under-replicated (3/5). This is independent of the upgrade. Quorum is maintained (2 of 3 nodes).\n\n### 1.5 Topology\n\n- 3 pods, all on node `karma-2-control-plane` (single-node kind cluster)\n- Headless service `crdb-cluster` (grpc :26257, http :8080)\n- Public service `crdb-cluster-public` (ClusterIP 10.96.108.74)\n- No TLS (insecure mode)\n- No localities configured\n- No `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` set\n\n---\n\n## 2. What Changes in This Upgrade\n\n### 2.1 Target Version\n\nUpgrade from **v24.1.0** to **v24.2.x** (latest patch in the v24.2 minor series).\nCockroachDB follows a biannual release cadence; v24.2 is the next supported minor version after v24.1.\n\n> Before the maintenance window, confirm the exact patch tag (e.g. `v24.2.4`) by checking the\n> CockroachDB releases page and selecting the latest v24.2.x release.\n\n### 2.2 StatefulSet Image\n\nThe only required change to the Kubernetes manifest:\n\n```\nFROM: image: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n  TO: image: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>\n```\n\nAll other StatefulSet fields (replicas, resources, flags, services, PVCs) remain unchanged.\n\n### 2.3 Cluster Settings Changes During Window\n\n| Setting | Before Window | During Window | After Window |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` | *(empty)* | `'24.1'` | *(reset to empty)* |\n| `version` | 24.1 | 24.1 (pinned by preserve_downgrade) | 24.2 (auto-advances after reset) |\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | 1.0 MiB/s | 1.0 MiB/s (unchanged) | 1.0 MiB/s (unchanged) |\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | true | true (unchanged) | true (unchanged) |\n\nAll non-default cluster settings survive the upgrade unchanged; CockroachDB preserves them across versions.\n\n### 2.4 Zone Configurations\n\nZone configurations are stored in the cluster's system tables and persist across the upgrade unchanged. No zone config changes are planned.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Pre-Upgrade Checklist (Day-Of)\n\nRun all checks before touching any manifest. Do not proceed if any check fails.\n\n```bash\n# 1. Confirm all 3 nodes live and healthy\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --insecure\n\n# 2. Confirm no unexpected under-replicated ranges\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT range_id, replicas FROM crdb_internal.ranges_no_leases\n   WHERE array_length(replicas,1) < num_replicas LIMIT 10;\"\n# Expected: rows only for meta/system/liveness ranges (pre-existing 3-of-5)\n\n# 3. Confirm no active schema changes or long-running jobs\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT job_id, job_type, status FROM crdb_internal.jobs\n   WHERE status IN ('running','paused')\n     AND job_type != 'AUTO SQL STATS COMPACTION';\"\n\n# 4. Confirm cluster logical version is 24.1\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n\n# 5. Confirm rebalance throttle is still 1.0 MiB\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate;\"\n\n# 6. Confirm preserve_downgrade_option is empty\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Upgrade Procedure\n\n### Step 1 — Pin the downgrade option (enables rollback)\n\nSetting this prevents the cluster from auto-finalizing to v24.2 before all nodes\nare updated and verified. Must be set before any pod is restarted.\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SET CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option = '24.1';\"\n```\n\nVerify:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n# Expected: 24.1\n```\n\n### Step 2 — Update the StatefulSet image\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>\n```\n\nThe RollingUpdate strategy (partition: 0) will restart pods one at a time in\nreverse ordinal order: crdb-cluster-2 -> crdb-cluster-1 -> crdb-cluster-0.\nEach pod pulls the new image, starts the new binary, and rejoins the cluster.\n\n### Step 3 — Monitor the rolling restart\n\n```bash\n# Watch rollout progress\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster\n\n# After each pod restarts, check it rejoins on the new version\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --insecure\n```\n\nExpected: each node shows the new build tag within ~60 s of restart.\nThe cluster logical version remains at 24.1 throughout this step (pinned by preserve_downgrade_option).\n\n> **Rebalance throttle impact:** `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` is 1.0 MiB/s (vs default\n> 32 MiB/s). With 10 Gi data per pod the worst-case rebalancing after a node restart is\n> approximately 10,000 MiB / 1 MiB/s = ~2.8 hours per node. Plan the maintenance window\n> accordingly, or temporarily raise the throttle (see Section 7).\n\n### Step 4 — Verify all nodes are on v24.2\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT node_id, address, build_tag FROM crdb_internal.gossip_nodes;\"\n# All 3 nodes must show v24.2.x before proceeding to Step 5\n```\n\n### Step 5 — Finalize the upgrade\n\nOnce all nodes are on v24.2 and the cluster is healthy, release the downgrade pin\nto allow the cluster to advance its logical version to 24.2:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"RESET CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n```\n\nWait for the logical version to advance:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n# Expected: 24.2\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Post-Upgrade Verification\n\n```bash\n# 1. Binary version on all nodes\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach version\n\n# 2. Cluster logical version finalized at 24.2\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n\n# 3. All 3 nodes live\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --insecure\n\n# 4. Non-default settings preserved\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings\n   WHERE value != default_value;\"\n# Expected: kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate=1.0 MiB, diagnostics.reporting.enabled=true\n# cluster.preserve_downgrade_option must be ABSENT (back to default)\n\n# 5. Zone configs preserved\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones;\"\n\n# 6. No ERROR or FATAL in logs post-restart\nkubectl -n cockroachdb logs crdb-cluster-0 --since=30m | grep -E 'ERROR|FATAL'\nkubectl -n cockroachdb logs crdb-cluster-1 --since=30m | grep -E 'ERROR|FATAL'\nkubectl -n cockroachdb logs crdb-cluster-2 --since=30m | grep -E 'ERROR|FATAL'\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Rollback Plan\n\nRollback is possible **only before Step 5** (finalize). Once `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option`\nis reset and the cluster logical version advances to 24.2, rollback is not supported.\n\n```bash\n# Rollback: revert image to v24.1.0 while preserve_downgrade_option = '24.1'\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n\n# Monitor rollback\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster\n\n# Once all pods are back on v24.1.0 and verified healthy, clear the pin\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"RESET CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Optional: Temporarily Raise Rebalance Throttle During Window\n\nThe current `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 1.0 MiB/s` is 32x below the default.\nIf the maintenance window is time-constrained, temporarily raise the rate to speed up\npost-restart rebalancing, then restore the custom value afterward.\n\nThis change must be separately reviewed and approved before executing.\n\n```sql\n-- At window start (after Step 1, before Step 2)\nSET CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = '32 MiB';\n\n-- At window end (after Step 5, post-verification)\nSET CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = '1.0 MiB';\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Node fails to rejoin after restart | Low | Medium | Rollback to v24.1.0 per Section 6; pod restart policy handles transient failures |\n| Rebalancing takes longer than window | Medium | Low | Plan window for ~3 h per node at 1 MiB/s throttle, or raise throttle (Section 7) |\n| Under-replicated system ranges worsen during upgrade | Low | Low | Already under-replicated pre-upgrade (5 wanted, 3 available); quorum maintained at 2/3 throughout |\n| Upgrade auto-finalizes before all nodes updated | None | High | Prevented by setting `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option = '24.1'` in Step 1 |\n| v24.2 behavioral changes break workloads | Low | Medium | Test against v24.2 in a non-production cluster before the production window |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Summary of Changes\n\n| Component | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| Container image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>` |\n| Cluster logical version | 24.1 | 24.2 |\n| `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` | *(unset)* | Set to `'24.1'` during window; reset after verification |\n| All other settings, zone configs, replicas, resources | Unchanged | Unchanged |\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":113,"newStart":1,"newLines":323,"lines":["-# RabbitMQ Cluster — Upgrade & Configuration Migration Plan","+# CockroachDB Minor-Version Upgrade Change Plan","+## v24.1.0 → v24.2.x"," ","-**Namespace:** `karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-af2b323e-cluster-a`","-**Prepared:** 2026-06-18","-**Status:** PLANNING ONLY — no changes applied. Live cluster left exactly as found.","+**Prepared:** 2026-06-23","+**Status:** REVIEW ONLY — do not execute until approved","+**Namespace:** cockroachdb","+**Cluster:** crdb-cluster (3-node StatefulSet)"," "," ---"," ","-## 1. Current State (as inspected)","+## 1. Current Cluster Snapshot"," ","-### Topology & Platform","-- **Workload:** StatefulSet `rabbitmq`, 3/3 replicas (`rabbitmq-0..2`), all Running.","-  - `updateStrategy: RollingUpdate`, `podManagementPolicy: OrderedReady`.","-- **Image:** `rabbitmq:3.12-management` → resolved version **RabbitMQ 3.12.14 on Erlang/OTP 25 (erts 13.2.2.11 / 25.3.2.15)**.","-- **Release support:** RabbitMQ **3.12 series is OUT OF SUPPORT** (per node status output). This is the primary driver for the upgrade.","-- **Cluster:** 3 disk nodes, all Running, no maintenance, **no alarms**.","-- **Storage:** No PVCs returned in namespace — data appears to be on `emptyDir`/ephemeral volumes (mnesia under `/var/lib/rabbitmq/mnesia`). **Verify before upgrade** — ephemeral storage means a full StatefulSet replace would lose definitions/messages.","-- **Plugins enabled:** `rabbitmq_management`, `rabbitmq_management_agent`, `rabbitmq_prometheus`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_common`, `rabbitmq_web_dispatch`.","+### 1.1 Version"," ","-### Virtual Hosts","-| vhost | purpose |","-|-------|---------|","-| `/`   | default (admin only) |","-| `/app`| application traffic |","-| `/ops`| operations traffic |","+| Field | Value |","+|---|---|","+| Binary version | v24.1.0 (built 2024-05-15) |","+| Active cluster version | 24.1 |","+| Distribution | CCL (Community + Enterprise) |","+| Platform | linux amd64 |"," ","-### Users & Permissions","-| user | tags | permissions |","-|------|------|-------------|","-| `admin` | administrator | full `.* .* .*` on `/`, `/app`, `/ops` |","-| `app-user` | management | full `.* .* .*` on `/app` |","-| `ops-user` | management | full `.* .* .*` on `/ops` |","+### 1.2 StatefulSet"," ","-### Policies","-| vhost | name | pattern | apply-to | definition | priority |","-|-------|------|---------|----------|------------|----------|","-| `/app` | `ha-all` | `^app-queue$` | queues | `{\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"}` | 0 |","-| `/` , `/ops` | (none) | | | | |","+| Field | Current Value |","+|---|---|","+| Replicas | 3 (crdb-cluster-0/1/2) |","+| Container image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` |","+| CPU request/limit | 1 core |","+| Memory request/limit | 2 Gi |","+| Storage per pod | 10 Gi (RWO, storageclass: standard) |","+| Cache flag | `--cache=25%` (~512 MiB) |","+| Max SQL memory flag | `--max-sql-memory=25%` (~512 MiB) |","+| Security mode | `--insecure` |","+| Update strategy | RollingUpdate (partition: 0) |","+| Pod management | Parallel |","+| Termination grace period | 10 s |"," ","-### Queues","-| vhost | queue | type | durable | arguments |","-|-------|-------|------|---------|-----------|","-| `/app` | `app-queue` | classic | true | `x-queue-type=classic` |","-| `/ops` | `ops-queue` | classic | true | `x-queue-type=classic` |","+### 1.3 Non-Default Cluster Settings"," ","-### Feature Flags","-All flags **enabled**, including `quorum_queue`, `stream_queue`, `classic_mirrored_queue_version`, `feature_flags_v2`, `virtual_host_metadata`, `user_limits`. (All-enabled is a precondition for upgrading to the next minor.)","+| Variable | Current Value | Default | Notes |","+|---|---|---|---|","+| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | 1.0 MiB/s | 32 MiB/s | Deliberately throttled; limits rebalancing and upreplication snapshot bandwidth |","+| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | true | false | Explicitly enabled; sends diagnostic telemetry to Cockroach Labs |","+| `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` | *(not set)* | *(empty)* | Not set; upgrade auto-finalizes once all nodes are on the new binary |","+| `version` | 24.1 | — | Cluster logical version; advances automatically after all nodes upgrade |"," ","+### 1.4 Zone Configurations","+","+| Target | num_replicas | gc.ttlseconds | range_min_bytes | range_max_bytes |","+|---|---|---|---|---|","+| RANGE default | 3 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |","+| RANGE meta | 5 | 3600 (1 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |","+| RANGE system | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |","+| RANGE liveness | 5 | 600 (10 min) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |","+| DATABASE system | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |","+| TABLE system.public.lease | *(inherited)* | 600 (10 min) | — | — |","+| TABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats | *(inherited)* | 600 (10 min) | — | — |","+| TABLE system.public.replication_stats | *(inherited)* | 600 (10 min) | — | — |","+| TABLE system.public.statement_statistics | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |","+| TABLE system.public.transaction_statistics | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |","+| TABLE system.public.tenant_usage | *(inherited)* | 7200 (2 h) | — | — |","+| TABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |","+| TABLE system.public.statement_activity | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |","+| TABLE system.public.transaction_activity | *(inherited)* | 3600 (1 h) | — | — |","+","+> **Pre-existing under-replication:** meta, system, liveness, and system database ranges are","+> configured for 5 replicas but the cluster has only 3 nodes. These ranges are permanently","+> under-replicated (3/5). This is independent of the upgrade. Quorum is maintained (2 of 3 nodes).","+","+### 1.5 Topology","+","+- 3 pods, all on node `karma-2-control-plane` (single-node kind cluster)","+- Headless service `crdb-cluster` (grpc :26257, http :8080)","+- Public service `crdb-cluster-public` (ClusterIP 10.96.108.74)","+- No TLS (insecure mode)","+- No localities configured","+- No `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` set","+"," ---"," ","-## 2. KEY RISK — Classic Mirrored Queues","+## 2. What Changes in This Upgrade"," ","-The `/app` policy **`ha-all`** uses `ha-mode: all` — this is **classic queue mirroring (HA)**.","+### 2.1 Target Version"," ","-- Classic mirroring is **deprecated in 3.13** and **removed in RabbitMQ 4.0**.","-- The `classic_mirrored_queue_version` feature flag and any `ha-*` policy must be retired before reaching 4.x.","-- `app-queue` is an explicitly classic queue mirrored by this policy.","+Upgrade from **v24.1.0** to **v24.2.x** (latest patch in the v24.2 minor series).","+CockroachDB follows a biannual release cadence; v24.2 is the next supported minor version after v24.1."," ","-**This is the central migration item.** The recommended target is to migrate `app-queue` to a **quorum queue** (the supported replacement for HA classic queues). Quorum queues cannot be converted in place — they require create-new + drain/republish.","+> Before the maintenance window, confirm the exact patch tag (e.g. `v24.2.4`) by checking the","+> CockroachDB releases page and selecting the latest v24.2.x release."," ","+### 2.2 StatefulSet Image","+","+The only required change to the Kubernetes manifest:","+","+```","+FROM: image: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0","+  TO: image: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>","+```","+","+All other StatefulSet fields (replicas, resources, flags, services, PVCs) remain unchanged.","+","+### 2.3 Cluster Settings Changes During Window","+","+| Setting | Before Window | During Window | After Window |","+|---|---|---|---|","+| `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` | *(empty)* | `'24.1'` | *(reset to empty)* |","+| `version` | 24.1 | 24.1 (pinned by preserve_downgrade) | 24.2 (auto-advances after reset) |","+| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | 1.0 MiB/s | 1.0 MiB/s (unchanged) | 1.0 MiB/s (unchanged) |","+| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | true | true (unchanged) | true (unchanged) |","+","+All non-default cluster settings survive the upgrade unchanged; CockroachDB preserves them across versions.","+","+### 2.4 Zone Configurations","+","+Zone configurations are stored in the cluster's system tables and persist across the upgrade unchanged. No zone config changes are planned.","+"," ---"," ","-## 3. Recommended Upgrade Path","+## 3. Pre-Upgrade Checklist (Day-Of)"," ","-RabbitMQ supports upgrades only between **adjacent minor versions**. Do not jump 3.12 → 4.0 directly.","+Run all checks before touching any manifest. Do not proceed if any check fails."," ","+```bash","+# 1. Confirm all 3 nodes live and healthy","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\","+  ./cockroach node status --insecure","+","+# 2. Confirm no unexpected under-replicated ranges","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","+  \"SELECT range_id, replicas FROM crdb_internal.ranges_no_leases","+   WHERE array_length(replicas,1) < num_replicas LIMIT 10;\"","+# Expected: rows only for meta/system/liveness ranges (pre-existing 3-of-5)","+","+# 3. Confirm no active schema changes or long-running jobs","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","+  \"SELECT job_id, job_type, status FROM crdb_internal.jobs","+   WHERE status IN ('running','paused')","+     AND job_type != 'AUTO SQL STATS COMPACTION';\"","+","+# 4. Confirm cluster logical version is 24.1","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","+  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"","+","+# 5. Confirm rebalance throttle is still 1.0 MiB","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","+  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate;\"","+","+# 6. Confirm preserve_downgrade_option is empty","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","+  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\""," ```","-3.12.14  →  3.13.x (latest patch)  →  4.0.x  →  4.1.x (target)","+","+---","+","+## 4. Upgrade Procedure","+","+### Step 1 — Pin the downgrade option (enables rollback)","+","+Setting this prevents the cluster from auto-finalizing to v24.2 before all nodes","+are updated and verified. Must be set before any pod is restarted.","+","+```bash","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","+  \"SET CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option = '24.1';\""," ```"," ","-### Phase 0 — Pre-flight (no downtime)","-1. Confirm **all feature flags enabled** (already true) — required before each minor bump.","-2. **Confirm persistence:** verify mnesia data survives pod restart. If on `emptyDir`, FIRST migrate the StatefulSet to PVC-backed `volumeClaimTemplates` (separate change) — otherwise a rolling upgrade that recreates pods risks data loss.","-3. Export full definitions backup: `rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/defs.json` (or via management API) and copy off-cluster.","-4. Snapshot current state (this document) and stop non-essential producers if a maintenance window allows.","+Verify:"," ","-### Phase 1 — Upgrade 3.12.14 → 3.13.x","-- Bump image to `rabbitmq:3.13-management` (pin a specific patch, e.g. `3.13.7-management`).","-- Rolling restart honoring `OrderedReady` (pods restart `rabbitmq-2` → `-1` → `-0`); wait for each node to fully rejoin (`rabbitmqctl cluster_status`, no alarms, queues synced) before the next.","-- After all nodes on 3.13: re-run `rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all`.","-- 3.13 still supports mirroring (deprecated) — cluster remains functional. **Mirroring removal happens here, before 4.0.**","+```bash","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","+  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"","+# Expected: 24.1","+```"," ","-### Phase 2 — Remove classic mirroring / migrate `app-queue`","-- Create a new quorum queue (e.g. `app-queue-qq`) in `/app` with `x-queue-type: quorum`.","-- Repoint producers/consumers, drain `app-queue`, then delete the old queue and the `ha-all` policy. (Alternatively shovel messages across.)","-- Confirm no `ha-*` policies and no mirrored queues remain (`rabbitmqctl list_policies`, management UI \"Queues\" shows no mirrors).","+### Step 2 — Update the StatefulSet image"," ","-### Phase 3 — Upgrade 3.13.x → 4.0.x → 4.1.x","-- Repeat the rolling-restart procedure per minor bump; enable all feature flags after each.","-- 4.0 requires mirroring already gone (Phase 2) and all flags enabled.","-- Validate after each step: cluster_status, no alarms, all vhosts/users/permissions/queues present, app + ops traffic healthy.","+```bash","+kubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\","+  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>","+```"," ","+The RollingUpdate strategy (partition: 0) will restart pods one at a time in","+reverse ordinal order: crdb-cluster-2 -> crdb-cluster-1 -> crdb-cluster-0.","+Each pod pulls the new image, starts the new binary, and rejoins the cluster.","+","+### Step 3 — Monitor the rolling restart","+","+```bash","+# Watch rollout progress","+kubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster","+","+# After each pod restarts, check it rejoins on the new version","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\","+  ./cockroach node status --insecure","+```","+","+Expected: each node shows the new build tag within ~60 s of restart.","+The cluster logical version remains at 24.1 throughout this step (pinned by preserve_downgrade_option).","+","+> **Rebalance throttle impact:** `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` is 1.0 MiB/s (vs default","+> 32 MiB/s). With 10 Gi data per pod the worst-case rebalancing after a node restart is","+> approximately 10,000 MiB / 1 MiB/s = ~2.8 hours per node. Plan the maintenance window","+> accordingly, or temporarily raise the throttle (see Section 7).","+","+### Step 4 — Verify all nodes are on v24.2","+","+```bash","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","+  \"SELECT node_id, address, build_tag FROM crdb_internal.gossip_nodes;\"","+# All 3 nodes must show v24.2.x before proceeding to Step 5","+```","+","+### Step 5 — Finalize the upgrade","+","+Once all nodes are on v24.2 and the cluster is healthy, release the downgrade pin","+to allow the cluster to advance its logical version to 24.2:","+","+```bash","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","+  \"RESET CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"","+```","+","+Wait for the logical version to advance:","+","+```bash","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","+  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"","+# Expected: 24.2","+```","+"," ---"," ","-## 4. Configuration Migration Checklist (to reapply / verify post-upgrade)","-- [ ] vhosts: `/`, `/app`, `/ops` present.","-- [ ] users: `admin` (administrator), `app-user` (management), `ops-user` (management) with passwords/permissions intact.","-- [ ] permissions: admin on all three vhosts; app-user on `/app`; ops-user on `/ops`.","-- [ ] queues: `ops-queue` (classic, durable) present; `app-queue` migrated to quorum (Phase 2).","-- [ ] policies: `ha-all` **removed** after migration; add a quorum-queue policy if HA semantics still needed (quorum queues are inherently replicated — usually no policy required).","-- [ ] plugins all re-enabled; Prometheus scraping intact (`prometheus` pod present in namespace).","-- [ ] feature flags all enabled.","+## 5. Post-Upgrade Verification"," ","-## 5. Rollback","-- Per minor: if a node fails to rejoin, halt the rolling upgrade, restore the failed node from the prior image, and verify cluster_status. RabbitMQ does **not** support in-place downgrade across minors — rollback = redeploy prior image + `import_definitions` from the Phase 0 backup into a freshly initialized cluster.","-- Keep the Phase 0 definitions export and (if PVC-backed) a volume snapshot for the duration of the change window.","+```bash","+# 1. Binary version on all nodes","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach version"," ","-## 6. Recommended Change-Window Sequence (summary)","-1. Backup definitions + confirm persistence.","-2. 3.12 → 3.13, enable flags.","-3. Migrate `app-queue` to quorum, drop `ha-all`.","-4. 3.13 → 4.0 → 4.1, enabling flags each step.","-5. Run full config checklist + smoke test app/ops traffic.","+# 2. Cluster logical version finalized at 24.2","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","+  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"","+","+# 3. All 3 nodes live","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\","+  ./cockroach node status --insecure","+","+# 4. Non-default settings preserved","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","+  \"SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings","+   WHERE value != default_value;\"","+# Expected: kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate=1.0 MiB, diagnostics.reporting.enabled=true","+# cluster.preserve_downgrade_option must be ABSENT (back to default)","+","+# 5. Zone configs preserved","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","+  \"SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones;\"","+","+# 6. No ERROR or FATAL in logs post-restart","+kubectl -n cockroachdb logs crdb-cluster-0 --since=30m | grep -E 'ERROR|FATAL'","+kubectl -n cockroachdb logs crdb-cluster-1 --since=30m | grep -E 'ERROR|FATAL'","+kubectl -n cockroachdb logs crdb-cluster-2 --since=30m | grep -E 'ERROR|FATAL'","+```","+","+---","+","+## 6. Rollback Plan","+","+Rollback is possible **only before Step 5** (finalize). Once `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option`","+is reset and the cluster logical version advances to 24.2, rollback is not supported.","+","+```bash","+# Rollback: revert image to v24.1.0 while preserve_downgrade_option = '24.1'","+kubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\","+  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0","+","+# Monitor rollback","+kubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster","+","+# Once all pods are back on v24.1.0 and verified healthy, clear the pin","+kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\","+  \"RESET CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"","+```","+","+---","+","+## 7. Optional: Temporarily Raise Rebalance Throttle During Window","+","+The current `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 1.0 MiB/s` is 32x below the default.","+If the maintenance window is time-constrained, temporarily raise the rate to speed up","+post-restart rebalancing, then restore the custom value afterward.","+","+This change must be separately reviewed and approved before executing.","+","+```sql","+-- At window start (after Step 1, before Step 2)","+SET CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = '32 MiB';","+","+-- At window end (after Step 5, post-verification)","+SET CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = '1.0 MiB';","+```","+","+---","+","+## 8. Risk Assessment","+","+| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |","+|---|---|---|---|","+| Node fails to rejoin after restart | Low | Medium | Rollback to v24.1.0 per Section 6; pod restart policy handles transient failures |","+| Rebalancing takes longer than window | Medium | Low | Plan window for ~3 h per node at 1 MiB/s throttle, or raise throttle (Section 7) |","+| Under-replicated system ranges worsen during upgrade | Low | Low | Already under-replicated pre-upgrade (5 wanted, 3 available); quorum maintained at 2/3 throughout |","+| Upgrade auto-finalizes before all nodes updated | None | High | Prevented by setting `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option = '24.1'` in Step 1 |","+| v24.2 behavioral changes break workloads | Low | Medium | Test against v24.2 in a non-production cluster before the production window |","+","+---","+","+## 9. Summary of Changes","+","+| Component | Before | After |","+|---|---|---|","+| Container image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.<patch>` |","+| Cluster logical version | 24.1 | 24.2 |","+| `cluster.preserve_downgrade_option` | *(unset)* | Set to `'24.1'` during window; reset after verification |","+| All other settings, zone configs, replicas, resources | Unchanged | Unchanged |"]}],"originalFile":"# RabbitMQ Cluster — Upgrade & Configuration Migration Plan\n\n**Namespace:** `karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-af2b323e-cluster-a`\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-18\n**Status:** PLANNING ONLY — no changes applied. Live cluster left exactly as found.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State (as inspected)\n\n### Topology & Platform\n- **Workload:** StatefulSet `rabbitmq`, 3/3 replicas (`rabbitmq-0..2`), all Running.\n  - `updateStrategy: RollingUpdate`, `podManagementPolicy: OrderedReady`.\n- **Image:** `rabbitmq:3.12-management` → resolved version **RabbitMQ 3.12.14 on Erlang/OTP 25 (erts 13.2.2.11 / 25.3.2.15)**.\n- **Release support:** RabbitMQ **3.12 series is OUT OF SUPPORT** (per node status output). This is the primary driver for the upgrade.\n- **Cluster:** 3 disk nodes, all Running, no maintenance, **no alarms**.\n- **Storage:** No PVCs returned in namespace — data appears to be on `emptyDir`/ephemeral volumes (mnesia under `/var/lib/rabbitmq/mnesia`). **Verify before upgrade** — ephemeral storage means a full StatefulSet replace would lose definitions/messages.\n- **Plugins enabled:** `rabbitmq_management`, `rabbitmq_management_agent`, `rabbitmq_prometheus`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_common`, `rabbitmq_web_dispatch`.\n\n### Virtual Hosts\n| vhost | purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| `/`   | default (admin only) |\n| `/app`| application traffic |\n| `/ops`| operations traffic |\n\n### Users & Permissions\n| user | tags | permissions |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| `admin` | administrator | full `.* .* .*` on `/`, `/app`, `/ops` |\n| `app-user` | management | full `.* .* .*` on `/app` |\n| `ops-user` | management | full `.* .* .*` on `/ops` |\n\n### Policies\n| vhost | name | pattern | apply-to | definition | priority |\n|-------|------|---------|----------|------------|----------|\n| `/app` | `ha-all` | `^app-queue$` | queues | `{\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"}` | 0 |\n| `/` , `/ops` | (none) | | | | |\n\n### Queues\n| vhost | queue | type | durable | arguments |\n|-------|-------|------|---------|-----------|\n| `/app` | `app-queue` | classic | true | `x-queue-type=classic` |\n| `/ops` | `ops-queue` | classic | true | `x-queue-type=classic` |\n\n### Feature Flags\nAll flags **enabled**, including `quorum_queue`, `stream_queue`, `classic_mirrored_queue_version`, `feature_flags_v2`, `virtual_host_metadata`, `user_limits`. (All-enabled is a precondition for upgrading to the next minor.)\n\n---\n\n## 2. KEY RISK — Classic Mirrored Queues\n\nThe `/app` policy **`ha-all`** uses `ha-mode: all` — this is **classic queue mirroring (HA)**.\n\n- Classic mirroring is **deprecated in 3.13** and **removed in RabbitMQ 4.0**.\n- The `classic_mirrored_queue_version` feature flag and any `ha-*` policy must be retired before reaching 4.x.\n- `app-queue` is an explicitly classic queue mirrored by this policy.\n\n**This is the central migration item.** The recommended target is to migrate `app-queue` to a **quorum queue** (the supported replacement for HA classic queues). Quorum queues cannot be converted in place — they require create-new + drain/republish.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Recommended Upgrade Path\n\nRabbitMQ supports upgrades only between **adjacent minor versions**. Do not jump 3.12 → 4.0 directly.\n\n```\n3.12.14  →  3.13.x (latest patch)  →  4.0.x  →  4.1.x (target)\n```\n\n### Phase 0 — Pre-flight (no downtime)\n1. Confirm **all feature flags enabled** (already true) — required before each minor bump.\n2. **Confirm persistence:** verify mnesia data survives pod restart. If on `emptyDir`, FIRST migrate the StatefulSet to PVC-backed `volumeClaimTemplates` (separate change) — otherwise a rolling upgrade that recreates pods risks data loss.\n3. Export full definitions backup: `rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/defs.json` (or via management API) and copy off-cluster.\n4. Snapshot current state (this document) and stop non-essential producers if a maintenance window allows.\n\n### Phase 1 — Upgrade 3.12.14 → 3.13.x\n- Bump image to `rabbitmq:3.13-management` (pin a specific patch, e.g. `3.13.7-management`).\n- Rolling restart honoring `OrderedReady` (pods restart `rabbitmq-2` → `-1` → `-0`); wait for each node to fully rejoin (`rabbitmqctl cluster_status`, no alarms, queues synced) before the next.\n- After all nodes on 3.13: re-run `rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all`.\n- 3.13 still supports mirroring (deprecated) — cluster remains functional. **Mirroring removal happens here, before 4.0.**\n\n### Phase 2 — Remove classic mirroring / migrate `app-queue`\n- Create a new quorum queue (e.g. `app-queue-qq`) in `/app` with `x-queue-type: quorum`.\n- Repoint producers/consumers, drain `app-queue`, then delete the old queue and the `ha-all` policy. (Alternatively shovel messages across.)\n- Confirm no `ha-*` policies and no mirrored queues remain (`rabbitmqctl list_policies`, management UI \"Queues\" shows no mirrors).\n\n### Phase 3 — Upgrade 3.13.x → 4.0.x → 4.1.x\n- Repeat the rolling-restart procedure per minor bump; enable all feature flags after each.\n- 4.0 requires mirroring already gone (Phase 2) and all flags enabled.\n- Validate after each step: cluster_status, no alarms, all vhosts/users/permissions/queues present, app + ops traffic healthy.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Configuration Migration Checklist (to reapply / verify post-upgrade)\n- [ ] vhosts: `/`, `/app`, `/ops` present.\n- [ ] users: `admin` (administrator), `app-user` (management), `ops-user` (management) with passwords/permissions intact.\n- [ ] permissions: admin on all three vhosts; app-user on `/app`; ops-user on `/ops`.\n- [ ] queues: `ops-queue` (classic, durable) present; `app-queue` migrated to quorum (Phase 2).\n- [ ] policies: `ha-all` **removed** after migration; add a quorum-queue policy if HA semantics still needed (quorum queues are inherently replicated — usually no policy required).\n- [ ] plugins all re-enabled; Prometheus scraping intact (`prometheus` pod present in namespace).\n- [ ] feature flags all enabled.\n\n## 5. Rollback\n- Per minor: if a node fails to rejoin, halt the rolling upgrade, restore the failed node from the prior image, and verify cluster_status. RabbitMQ does **not** support in-place downgrade across minors — rollback = redeploy prior image + `import_definitions` from the Phase 0 backup into a freshly initialized cluster.\n- Keep the Phase 0 definitions export and (if PVC-backed) a volume snapshot for the duration of the change window.\n\n## 6. Recommended Change-Window Sequence (summary)\n1. Backup definitions + confirm persistence.\n2. 3.12 → 3.13, enable flags.\n3. Migrate `app-queue` to quorum, drop `ha-all`.\n4. 3.13 → 4.0 → 4.1, enabling flags each step.\n5. Run full config checklist + smoke test app/ops traffic.\n","userModified":false}}
